data.meta_description: Cher Thala - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Cherthala is a town located in Alappuzha district in the state of Kerala, India. It is located 30 km south of Kochi and 22 km north of Alappuzha. Cherthala has a population of over 43,000 people and has a literacy rate of 94%. The town is well known for the Karthyayani Devi temple located at its center. Cherthala has also been proposed as a future satellite town for the expanding city of Kochi. It has important local industries like coir and has produced prominent political leaders.
